type.formalDescription: Admitted student's access to Cal Central
An individual who has graduated or is no longer active as a Student.
Applied for admission to UC Berkeley.

reason.formalDescription: Refund temporarily on hold pending administrative review. No action required at this time.

reason.description: No ID Provided at Cal 1 Card
reason.formalDescription: A government issue ID is required to receive a Cal 1 Card. A temporary Cal 1 Card was granted because you could not provide the required ID. You must provide a valid government issue ID to the Office of the Registrar before enrolling for the next term.

Your eligibility to enroll is blocked by the Office of the Registrar at the Request of University Health Services.

To restore your eligibility, please visit University Health Services at the Tang Center, 2222 Bancroft Way.

Your student account has a past due balance. A hold is now placed against official registration for next semester. A hold prevents release of your transcript or diploma. Other campus services may also be withheld.

Use the My Finances tab to make an online payment. 

For billing questions, contact Cal Student Central at 510-664-9181 or open a case at https://studentcentral.berkeley.edu.
If you are a financial aid recipient, your financial aid will not disburse until your academic status has been determined by your college.
